Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to low broil. Wash and dry produce.

Place @pita bread{2} on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Divide @marinara{2.5%ounce} cup between pitas and spread out in an even layer. Top with as much @pepperoni{3.5%ounce} as you like. Sprinkle with @italian cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

Bake pita pizzas on middle rack until pita edges are golden brown and cheese melts, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} into sticks (like fries; ours were 3 inches long and 1⁄3 inch thick).

Trim and thinly slice @mini cucumber{1} into rounds.

Halve @red grapes{4.5%ounce} if desired.

Let pepperoni pita pizzas cool, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Cut pizzas into six slices each.

Drizzle pizzas with as much @buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%ounce} as you like.

To serve: Divide pepperoni pita pizzas between #plates{} and serve with carrot sticks, cucumber rounds, grapes, and any remaining dressing on the side.

To stash: Let pizzas cool completely before packing for lunch. Refrigerate everything in separate containers until ready to pack. Refrigerate any leftovers in an airtight container.

> This recipe is designed to provide lunch for multiple days. For each lunch meal, 3 servings and 6 servings are provided for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.

